summary: Do you think that Sansa and Daenerys will become bff in the next season? Or more precisely will Sansa become D's handmaiden?😃...
question: Do you think that Sansa and Daenerys will become bff in the next season? Or more precisely will Sansa become D's handmaiden?😃 I'm so worried in what D&D will turn Sansa into in D's favor. I expect Sansa will give away her chamber for her, and not be surprised if the whole north being charmed by their new queen.
answer:
No. First of all show Sansa doesn’t warm up to people easily. She’s become a loner in many ways. The idea that she’d gush over Daenerys is first out of character and second contradicts Sansa’s reactions to Daenerys. She publicly told Jon not to go to Daenerys himself because of the Daenerys’ father’s actions. She was annoyed that Jon didn’t return quickly. She was also very annoyed at Jon for kneeling and the possibility that he would marry Daenerys. 

Daenerys coming North brings a lot of problems for Sansa. Food shortage for one, since Winterfell will have to feed the Dothraki, Unsullied and two large dragons, along with its residents while also acting as a reserve in case other places in the North run out of food. Daenerys will also come to the North believing that she’s their queen since Jon knelt and would try to win over the Northern houses. I’m not talking arrogance, I’m talking politically Daenerys needs why they should accept her as queen. This will inevitably mean stepping on Sansa’s shoes since Sansa has been acting as ruler of the North for a while to the point that many lords wanted to crown her queen. Daenerys cannot defer to Sansa’s authority and Sansa will not stand back meekly. That’s just the first episode. The politics the directors and showrunners have talked about isn’t going to be Cersei vs Daenerys.

Then again, this show tends to hype Sansa disagreeing with people a lot and it gets resolved in one or two episodes so who knows?

summary: I’m really sorry if I’m late to the party and someone’s already posted about this, but I just watched this little interview with...
caption:
I’m really sorry if I’m late to the party and someone’s already posted about this, but I just watched this little interview with Tom Wlaschiha which was conducted at Geek & Game Rio Festival, July 2018, and I think he’s accidentally revealed something.

Now, I know that Tom’s been spotted and photographed at GoT S8 filming locations earlier this year, but it all seemed very suspect. After all, GoT creators have a track record of re-hiring past actors under false pretences, simply to be seen wandering around on set, to throw fans off the spoiler scent.

But watch the above interview. It has terrible sound quality but right at the beginning, he says that he does know how GoT S8 ends, but he’s not going to tell what it is. Now, unless he’s outright lying, surely the producers wouldn’t reveal the ending to an actor that wasn’t actually genuinely involved in the shoot, right?

Guys. I think he’s in S8.
